item.description:
For the code fragment below,
//ch1.c #include &quot;stdio.h&quot; int main(int argc, char const *argv[]) { int a = 1; int c = (a=a * 2) + (a = a + 3); printf(&quot;a = %d, c = %d.\n&quot;, a, c); return 0; }  if gcc is used to compile it, there are no errors or warnings. Run the binary file and we will get:
 a = 5, c = 10.
